done anything remotely like that.

498
00:46:20,189 --> 00:46:23,385
I paid the guy everything he wanted.
Never happened before or since.

499
00:46:23,548 --> 00:46:25,458
-Okay. Okay.
-Okay.

500
00:46:27,773 --> 00:46:30,140
-Amy.
-What?

501
00:46:32,188 --> 00:46:34,457
Only you, me and the lawyers
know about that, right?

502
00:46:34,749 --> 00:46:36,123
Right.

503
00:46:36,284 --> 00:46:38,554
Because you haven't said
anything to Ted. Surely not.

504
00:46:38,717 --> 00:46:39,993
No.

505
00:46:40,285 --> 00:46:42,586
-Have you said something to Ted?
-Come on!

506
00:46:44,220 --> 00:46:46,009
Well, do I have timing or what?

507
00:46:46,173 --> 00:46:47,580
Yes, you do.

508
00:46:47,741 --> 00:46:50,611
Sorry you had to miss that.
I know how much you like my things.

509
00:46:50,780 --> 00:46:53,333
-Oh, Jesus.
-You and me are gonna have a talk.

510
00:46:53,501 --> 00:46:55,508
Be back in 1 0 minutes.

511
00:46:56,765 --> 00:46:58,620
I'm in trouble.

512
00:47:02,589 --> 00:47:05,851
-I've had enough of your bullshit.
-You're a dick.

513
00:47:06,652 --> 00:47:08,245
Do you feel better?

514
00:47:08,412 --> 00:47:09,656
Yes, I do.

515
00:47:09,821 --> 00:47:13,847
Yeah, look, marriages end.
I'm sorry, but I didn't end yours.

516
00:47:14,013 --> 00:47:15,769
It was done by the time I got there.

517
00:47:15,933 --> 00:47:18,803
Really? You must've thought her
wedding ring was a little strange.

518
00:47:18,972 --> 00:47:22,649
Oh, man. Listen, I apologized
to you months ago.

519
00:47:22,812 --> 00:47:26,838
I know you don't want me in your life.
I don't want you in mine either.

520
00:47:27,004 --> 00:47:30,266
But until this little divorce thing's
done, not much we can do about it.

521
00:47:30,429 --> 00:47:35,285
But I will not let you upset Amy
any more than you already have.

522
00:47:35,452 --> 00:47:39,031
So why don't we just wrap this thing
up and get out of each other's lives--?

523
00:47:42,076 --> 00:47:45,753
Are we getting the message
I'm sending?

524
00:47:46,909 --> 00:47:48,338
Where are we from, Teddy?

525
00:47:50,013 --> 00:47:51,354
Tennessee...

526
00:47:51,997 --> 00:47:53,207
...Morty.

527
00:47:55,004 --> 00:47:56,597
I was gonna say Mississippi.

528
00:47:57,309 --> 00:48:01,717
No. Long way from there.
Little place called Shooter's Bay.

529
00:48:21,341 --> 00:48:22,802
Come on, Karsch.

530
00:48:23,004 --> 00:48:26,201
Five hundred dollars a day.
Where are you when I need you?

531
00:48:52,348 --> 00:48:53,625
What--?

532
00:48:55,292 --> 00:48:57,202
What fresh hell...?

533
00:48:57,373 --> 00:48:59,674
-Yeah?
-Where you been all day?

534
00:49:00,636 --> 00:49:02,327
I might ask you the same question.

535
00:49:02,493 --> 00:49:05,308
Relax, you're fine.
I checked the cabin an hour ago.

536
00:49:05,469 --> 00:49:08,087
Well, he showed up an hour
after you left last night.

537
00:49:08,253 --> 00:49:10,293
Oh, really?
Then he had a busy night.

538
00:49:10,652 --> 00:49:13,522
My office called me about
your Riverdale house. I'm sorry.

539
00:49:13,693 --> 00:49:16,726
The worst part is, I hadn't had
a chance to get the magazine out.

540
00:49:16,893 --> 00:49:18,835
The one with the story he says I stole.

541
00:49:19,005 --> 00:49:20,412
That's gone up in smoke now.

542
00:49:20,573 --> 00:49:23,769
Do you still want to go through with it?
Meeting? Showing him the magazine?

543
00:49:23,932 --> 00:49:25,274
Hell, yes, man.

544
00:49:25,437 --> 00:49:28,786
I've had a shitty year.
I want it settled now. Everything.

545
00:49:28,957 --> 00:49:31,575
Good. I called your agent
when I heard about the house.

546
00:49:31,741 --> 00:49:34,010
I figured he'd have a copy
of the magazine.

547
00:49:34,173 --> 00:49:37,042
He sent the original by UPS
overnight today.

548
00:49:37,212 --> 00:49:38,968
You can pick it up tomorrow after 3.

549
00:49:39,132 --> 00:49:40,758
I knew there was a reason I hired you.

550
00:49:40,925 --> 00:49:42,102
There's something else.

551
00:49:42,909 --> 00:49:45,211
I caught up with your
Tom Greenleaf today.

552
00:49:45,373 --> 00:49:47,926
The guy who drove past you
and Shooter on the lake road.

553
00:49:48,092 --> 00:49:49,434
Well, he's a weird one.

554
00:49:49,596 --> 00:49:52,662
First he says he did go down
to the Lake Drive on Tuesday...

555
00:49:52,828 --> 00:49:54,617
...and he saw you like you said.

556
00:49:54,781 --> 00:49:56,723
But then he gets nervous and says:

557
00:49:56,893 --> 00:49:59,610
"No, come to think of it, I didn't.
Didn't see anybody.

558
00:49:59,773 --> 00:50:01,780
Wasn't even on Lake Drive
on Tuesday."

559
00:50:01,949 --> 00:50:05,909
Yeah, well, Tom's old.
Maybe just slipped his mind.

560
00:50:06,076 --> 00:50:07,320
Don't be naive.

561
00:50:07,484 --> 00:50:10,102
He was scared shitless.
Somebody got to him.

562
00:50:10,268 --> 00:50:11,829
Come on, wait.

563
00:50:11,997 --> 00:50:15,128
Why would Shooter care if
Tom Greenleaf knows he's here?

564
00:50:15,293 --> 00:50:17,660
-Well, it depends.
-On what?

565
00:50:17,821 --> 00:50:19,861
On what he plans to do to you.

566
00:50:20,028 --> 00:50:23,444
I'm revising my opinion, Mort.
I don't think Shooter's just some nut.

567
00:50:23,612 --> 00:50:27,769
We need to consider the possibility
that he was hired to do this.

568
00:50:27,933 --> 00:50:32,341
Somebody with a grudge against you
hires a tough guy to rattle you...

569
00:50:32,508 --> 00:50:34,232
...scare you to death.

570
00:50:34,397 --> 00:50:36,601
But he hires the wrong guy.

571
00:50:36,956 --> 00:50:38,996
Things get out of control.

572
00:50:39,164 --> 00:50:41,531
They go further than
they're supposed to.

573
00:50:41,692 --> 00:50:43,285
Dead dogs...

574
00:50:43,452 --> 00:50:45,362
...burnt-down houses.

575
00:50:45,980 --> 00:50:47,573
Now he can't call him off.

576
00:50:49,757 --> 00:50:51,829
-Ted.
-Who?

577
00:50:52,764 --> 00:50:54,171
Ted. Amy's Ted.

578
00:50:54,332 --> 00:50:56,569
The Ted that Amy left me for.

579
00:50:57,181 --> 00:51:00,279
That's why he calls himself Shooter.
Ted wants me to know it's him.

580
00:51:00,444 --> 00:51:03,128
He's trying to intimidate me,
trying to send me a message.

581
00:51:03,293 --> 00:51:05,529
-Why? What does he want?
-I don't know.

582
00:51:05,852 --> 00:51:07,543
Did you piss him off?

583
00:51:10,492 --> 00:51:12,729
-I might have.
-Okay, here's what we do.

584
00:51:13,468 --> 00:51:15,672
What proof do you have
that Shooter was there?

585
00:51:15,964 --> 00:51:19,609
Other than the manuscript.
Physical evidence, I'm talking about.

586
00:51:19,804 --> 00:51:23,100
Bruises. I got bruises on my arms
from where he grabbed me.

587
00:51:23,261 --> 00:51:24,635
All right.

588
00:51:25,756 --> 00:51:28,123
You and me are going to
go see Greenleaf together.

589
00:51:28,284 --> 00:51:29,462
All right.

590
00:51:29,629 --> 00:51:32,084
Bring the manuscript.
Bring your bruises.

591
00:51:32,253 --> 00:51:35,569
I'm gonna push the guy hard,
make it impossible for him to lie.

592
00:51:35,741 --> 00:51:38,643
If he'll tell the police he was
threatened too, we've got something.

593
00:51:39,933 --> 00:51:41,427
Bowie's store, breakfast?

594
00:51:41,597 --> 00:51:42,873
9 a.m. sharp.

595
00:51:43,036 --> 00:51:44,247
I'll see you there.

596
00:51:44,412 --> 00:51:45,841
And bring your six-gun, pilgrim.

597
00:51:57,340 --> 00:51:59,445
It is a good ending.

598
00:52:14,556 --> 00:52:16,149
Oh, shit.

599
00:52:46,204 --> 00:52:47,382
Shit.

600
00:54:06,109 --> 00:54:07,570
Pall Mall.

601
00:54:09,116 --> 00:54:10,393
Cracker bastard.

602
00:54:36,892 --> 00:54:38,168
Sorry.

603
00:54:45,500 --> 00:54:46,907
Ken?

604
00:54:52,604 --> 00:54:53,913
Tom?

605
00:55:19,996 --> 00:55:21,174
Would you like a pack?

606
00:55:22,236 --> 00:55:23,829
I don't smoke.

607
00:55:27,228 --> 00:55:29,562
Did a guy come in here
looking for me around 9:00?

608
00:55:29,725 --> 00:55:32,856
-No.
-Big guy, kind of a New York-cop type.

609
00:55:33,020 --> 00:55:34,962
No. No, that doesn't ring a bell.

610
00:55:35,133 --> 00:55:36,343
I overslept.

611
00:55:36,508 --> 00:55:39,355
Well, maybe he did too,
because he wasn't here.

612
00:55:41,468 --> 00:55:42,646
Yeah.

613
00:56:25,820 --> 00:56:26,997
What are you doing here?

614
00:56:27,164 --> 00:56:29,783
Matter of fact, I was just on my way
over to your place.

615
00:56:31,421 --> 00:56:32,598
Where's your buddy?

616
00:56:33,756 --> 00:56:36,341
-Came alone.
-Sure you did.

617
00:56:45,628 --> 00:56:46,872
I know what you're up to.

618
00:56:51,292 --> 00:56:52,917
Look, Mort....

619
00:56:53,980 --> 00:56:56,980
A lot of what's going on right now
is my fault.

620
00:56:57,341 --> 00:56:59,097
Most of it, in fact.

621
00:57:00,028 --> 00:57:01,205
What do you want?

622
00:57:03,709 --> 00:57:05,302
I want you out of our life.

623
00:57:06,908 --> 00:57:09,079
Gotta sign your papers, Mort.

624
00:57:12,284 --> 00:57:15,252
My divorce papers?
Tell her to send them to my lawyer.

625
00:57:15,420 --> 00:57:18,290
She did. He said that you won't return
his calls for weeks.

626
00:57:18,460 --> 00:57:20,981
-This is about the settlement?
-Just calm down.

627
00:57:21,148 --> 00:57:22,741
-Money?
-It's not about money.

628
00:57:22,909 --> 00:57:25,080
This is about getting this thing done.

629
00:57:25,244 --> 00:57:28,059
Because I'm afraid if we don't,
who knows where it might go.

630
00:57:28,220 --> 00:57:29,594
I think you know what I mean.

631
00:57:29,756 --> 00:57:32,244
Well, Teddy, I think I do,
but here's the problem:

632
00:57:32,412 --> 00:57:35,957
I don't respond well to intimidation.
Makes me feel icky. You know?

633
00:57:38,108 --> 00:57:41,305
You know, I'm attempting to have
a normal conversation here.

634
00:57:41,468 --> 00:57:42,995
I buried my dog, mister.

635
00:57:45,116 --> 00:57:48,149
This whole thing is out of your
control now. You know it, I know it.

636
00:57:48,316 --> 00:57:50,553
You started this shit,
I'm gonna finish it.

637
00:57:51,548 --> 00:57:55,225
Now, do me a favor, go back
and tell that to your filthy little friend.

638
00:57:57,500 --> 00:57:58,744
God!

639
00:57:59,452 --> 00:58:01,240
