649
01:00:35,580 --> 01:00:38,613
Now, I would have moved you,
but I didn't want to wake you.

650
01:00:38,780 --> 01:00:40,307
Got tired of waiting.

651
01:00:40,476 --> 01:00:43,378
Almost pinned a note on you.
Decided not to.

652
01:00:43,548 --> 01:00:45,075
You scare too easy.

653
01:00:45,723 --> 01:00:47,927
I wouldn't go too far if I were you.

654
01:00:48,092 --> 01:00:51,224
I hooked you to those two men
in more ways than you know.

655
01:00:51,388 --> 01:00:53,111
You're insane.
I'm going to the police.

656
01:00:53,276 --> 01:00:57,138
Whose screwdriver you think
is in that fella's head?

657
01:00:59,292 --> 01:01:01,332
If you leave them here
and I disappear...

658
01:01:01,500 --> 01:01:04,183
...you'll find yourself standing
with your head in the noose...

659
01:01:04,348 --> 01:01:06,323
...and your feet in Crisco.

660
01:01:06,908 --> 01:01:08,468
What do you want from me?

661
01:01:08,636 --> 01:01:11,091
Why, I told you that already,
Mr. Rainey.

662
01:01:11,260 --> 01:01:14,904
I want you to fix my story.
The one you stole.

663
01:01:15,068 --> 01:01:16,694
Or ain't you ready to admit it yet?

664
01:01:17,307 --> 01:01:20,374
I did not steal your story.

665
01:01:20,539 --> 01:01:24,249
I expect you'll let yourself
go to Greenhaven for murder...

666
01:01:24,412 --> 01:01:25,754
...before you'll admit it.

667
01:01:26,108 --> 01:01:28,180
I have the magazine, you lunatic!

668
01:01:28,348 --> 01:01:29,842
I have the magazine!

669
01:01:30,012 --> 01:01:33,176
I have the goddamn magazine!

670
01:01:33,340 --> 01:01:36,471
You have this so-called magazine
right now?

671
01:01:36,636 --> 01:01:38,643
On me, no.

672
01:01:39,004 --> 01:01:40,597
I was gonna go pick it up at 3:00.

673
01:01:41,307 --> 01:01:43,795
There can't be any magazine.

674
01:01:44,028 --> 01:01:47,640
Not with that story in it.
That story is mine.

675
01:01:48,444 --> 01:01:51,542
What do you want? To kill me?
Why don't you just do it? Just kill me.

676
01:01:51,708 --> 01:01:53,301
No, sir.

677
01:01:53,468 --> 01:01:56,218
These others here were gonna
get in the way of our business.

678
01:01:56,380 --> 01:01:58,136
I couldn't have that.

679
01:01:58,876 --> 01:02:01,145
You bring me that story...

680
01:02:01,563 --> 01:02:03,090
...if it exists.

681
01:02:03,260 --> 01:02:04,634
Your house in two hours.

682
01:02:04,796 --> 01:02:08,953
You got some heavy lifting here first.
I'd get to it if I were you.

683
01:02:09,499 --> 01:02:11,223
By the way...

684
01:02:11,388 --> 01:02:13,777
...if you talk to that sheriff
of yours again...

685
01:02:13,947 --> 01:02:16,795
...or if you don't show up at 4:00...

686
01:02:17,179 --> 01:02:19,863
...I will burn your life
and every person in it...

687
01:02:20,028 --> 01:02:22,897
...Iike a cane field in a high wind.

688
01:02:24,124 --> 01:02:27,190
When I show you the magazine that
has my name on the contents page...

689
01:02:27,356 --> 01:02:29,844
...with my story inside...

690
01:02:30,652 --> 01:02:33,270
-...then what?
-Then I turn myself in.

691
01:02:33,532 --> 01:02:36,532
But I'd take care of myself
before a trial, Mr. Rainey.

692
01:02:36,700 --> 01:02:38,740
Because if things turn out that way...

693
01:02:38,907 --> 01:02:41,493
...then I suppose I am crazy.

694
01:02:42,012 --> 01:02:44,052
And that kind of crazy man...

695
01:02:44,220 --> 01:02:47,187
...has no reason or excuse to live.

696
01:02:49,819 --> 01:02:51,314
Listen, you got my hat.

697
01:02:51,483 --> 01:02:54,418
I want it, one way or the other.

698
01:05:27,867 --> 01:05:29,972
-Hello?
-Mort?

699
01:05:30,716 --> 01:05:31,893
Yeah, hi.

700
01:05:32,188 --> 01:05:34,293
I've been so worried about you.
Are you okay?

701
01:05:34,460 --> 01:05:37,394
-I'm okay. I'm okay, Amy.
-Are you sure?

702
01:05:37,723 --> 01:05:41,171
When I saw you yesterday,
you seemed so strained. I mean....

703
01:05:43,068 --> 01:05:45,621
-What?
-Do you...?

704
01:05:47,067 --> 01:05:50,416
Do you think things would've been
different if we hadn't lost the baby?

705
01:05:51,228 --> 01:05:54,195
Jesus Christ, I don't--
Amy, I don't know.

706
01:05:54,364 --> 01:05:57,593
Let me call you later. I gotta go.
I gotta be somewhere.

707
01:05:59,451 --> 01:06:01,873
What? What is it, Amy?

708
01:06:03,547 --> 01:06:06,100
Breathe. Breathe.

709
01:06:06,267 --> 01:06:07,761
Take a breath.

710
01:06:09,532 --> 01:06:11,539
Where are you? You at Ted's?

711
01:06:11,708 --> 01:06:13,050
Yeah.

712
01:06:14,299 --> 01:06:16,536
How we feeling about
old Ted these days?

713
01:06:19,484 --> 01:06:21,207
I don't know.

714
01:06:22,491 --> 01:06:23,833
I love him, I guess.

715
01:06:27,324 --> 01:06:30,193
-That's good.
-I didn't go with other men, you know.

716
01:06:30,363 --> 01:06:32,949
I always wanted to tell you
that I didn't go with other men.

717
01:06:33,307 --> 01:06:36,690
Only T ed, and only the last few months
after you and me were already over.

718
01:06:36,860 --> 01:06:40,405
If we were over while we were still
together, you might've mentioned it...

719
01:06:40,571 --> 01:06:41,815
...because it was news to me.

720
01:06:41,980 --> 01:06:44,347
That's because you weren't
there anymore.

721
01:06:44,508 --> 01:06:45,970
You were gone all the time.

722
01:06:46,139 --> 01:06:47,666
I worked at home, Amy!

723
01:06:47,836 --> 01:06:50,356
That's not what I mean.

724
01:06:51,291 --> 01:06:53,779
Even when you were with me,
you were gone, up in your head.

725
01:06:53,948 --> 01:06:57,974
I don't think that I looked in your eyes
and saw you looking back at me...

726
01:06:58,140 --> 01:07:00,409
