How would he do that?

794
01:11:56,763 --> 01:11:58,388
I don't know...

795
01:11:59,611 --> 01:12:01,040
...but he did it.

796
01:12:01,787 --> 01:12:03,445
Think about it.

797
01:12:04,923 --> 01:12:06,232
How?

798
01:12:07,931 --> 01:12:09,622
I don't know.

799
01:12:50,972 --> 01:12:52,695
Why'd you put it on?

800
01:12:53,243 --> 01:12:54,705
I don't know.

801
01:12:55,195 --> 01:12:56,886
Maybe he wanted you to.

802
01:12:57,051 --> 01:12:59,123
Why would he want me
to put his hat on?

803
01:12:59,291 --> 01:13:01,047
Maybe he wants you to....

804
01:13:01,851 --> 01:13:03,444
Maybe he wants me to what?

805
01:13:04,443 --> 01:13:05,850
To get confused.

806
01:13:06,011 --> 01:13:09,273
Oh, I'm already confused, pilgrim.
Plenty confused.

807
01:13:09,468 --> 01:13:11,442
So don't talk to me about confusion.

808
01:13:11,611 --> 01:13:15,288
Wait a minute. Back up just a sec.
What about that?

809
01:13:15,643 --> 01:13:17,072
What about what?

810
01:13:17,243 --> 01:13:19,829
Well, "pilgrim." "Shooter's Bay."

811
01:13:19,995 --> 01:13:22,548
And the half a dozen other details
you've chosen to ignore.

812
01:13:22,715 --> 01:13:26,643
You know what? You're nuts. I don't
need to listen to this shit from you.

813
01:13:26,811 --> 01:13:28,753
Are all these things coincidences?

814
01:13:28,923 --> 01:13:30,963
I'm wearing his bruises, aren't l?

815
01:13:31,323 --> 01:13:33,745
-Aren't l?
-Are you?

816
01:13:34,747 --> 01:13:35,925
Well....

817
01:13:41,531 --> 01:13:43,287
This doesn't make any sense.

818
01:13:43,451 --> 01:13:47,281
Would you like to hear something that
does make sense? Call the police.

819
01:13:47,451 --> 01:13:50,866
Call Dave Newsome, tell him to come
here this second and lock you up...

820
01:13:51,035 --> 01:13:53,207
...before you can do
any more damage.

821
01:13:53,371 --> 01:13:55,543
I'm gonna get a knife
and cut you out of me.

822
01:13:56,315 --> 01:13:58,736
Before you kill anyone else.

823
01:13:59,707 --> 01:14:01,562
I didn't kill anybody.

824
01:14:07,035 --> 01:14:09,523
-You had a gun.
-Wasn't loaded.

825
01:14:09,691 --> 01:14:11,382
-Really?
-No.

826
01:14:11,547 --> 01:14:14,002
You almost killed them.
You wanted to.

827
01:14:14,171 --> 01:14:15,698
The gun was not loaded!

828
01:14:15,867 --> 01:14:17,525
-You still want to.
-Shut up!

829
01:14:17,691 --> 01:14:19,960
Listen to me.
Because this is how it happens.

830
01:14:20,123 --> 01:14:22,098
-This is how it happens to people.
-Shut up!

831
01:14:22,267 --> 01:14:24,755
There is no John Shooter.

832
01:14:26,268 --> 01:14:29,017
There never has been.
You invented him.

833
01:14:29,563 --> 01:14:32,312
Listen to me, not to him,
before it's too late.

834
01:14:32,475 --> 01:14:33,686
Leave me alone!

835
01:14:37,371 --> 01:14:39,259
You are alone.

836
01:14:59,387 --> 01:15:00,914
You're not handling this.

837
01:15:01,211 --> 01:15:02,553
What you're doing is wrong.

838
01:15:02,715 --> 01:15:04,176
You have no idea
what you're doing.

839
01:15:04,347 --> 01:15:08,657
You've been eating potato chips
this way for 30 years. For 30 years.

840
01:15:13,659 --> 01:15:15,634
Sister found out about
the broken window.

841
01:15:15,803 --> 01:15:18,007
The school had to be withdrawn
from the competition.

842
01:15:18,171 --> 01:15:20,854
Sister found out about
the broken windows.

843
01:15:21,019 --> 01:15:25,394
Then she got up from the table.
We didn't talk for the rest of the night.

844
01:15:25,595 --> 01:15:27,831
Todd Downey thought a woman
who'd steal your love--

845
01:15:27,995 --> 01:15:30,035
-What does Todd have to do with it?
-Everything.

846
01:15:30,203 --> 01:15:31,828
I'm starting to believe
Todd was right.

847
01:15:31,995 --> 01:15:34,362
Everything that you're doing
is wrong.

848
01:15:35,483 --> 01:15:37,338
What is happening to me?

849
01:15:37,755 --> 01:15:42,938
Oh, I think you know.
I think you have a real good idea.

850
01:15:43,707 --> 01:15:44,885
You don't exist.

851
01:15:45,051 --> 01:15:48,760
Me? I exist, Mr. Rainey.

852
01:15:49,595 --> 01:15:52,529
I exist because you made me.

853
01:15:52,827 --> 01:15:55,510
-Check it out.
-You thought me up.

854
01:15:55,675 --> 01:15:57,780
I'm a dairy farmer from Mississippi.

855
01:15:57,947 --> 01:15:59,540
Gave me my name.

856
01:15:59,867 --> 01:16:02,769
Told me everything
you wanted me to do.

857
01:16:15,099 --> 01:16:18,361
I did them things
so you wouldn't have to.

858
01:16:18,523 --> 01:16:20,694
Right up there, Tom.
We were standing right there.

859
01:16:20,859 --> 01:16:22,615
Yeah, I know, Mort. I saw you.

860
01:16:22,779 --> 01:16:25,496
I didn't want to say it in front of him,
but you were alone.

861
01:16:26,522 --> 01:16:30,646
I know, Tom. Look, just pull over for a
second. I want to show you something.

862
01:16:33,339 --> 01:16:37,333
Didn't have the stomach to do it
yourself, but you knew I did.

863
01:16:39,867 --> 01:16:41,241
Are we done yet?

864
01:16:41,403 --> 01:16:44,305
We got things all cleaned up
around here?

865
01:16:44,859 --> 01:16:47,412
What's the real reason I come for?

866
01:16:49,147 --> 01:16:51,962
-Fix the story.
-That's right.

867
01:16:52,955 --> 01:16:54,132
Fix the ending.

868
01:16:54,459 --> 01:16:55,801
Got to fix the ending.

869
01:16:55,963 --> 01:16:58,930
And how exactly do you suppose
we ought to do that?

870
01:17:22,683 --> 01:17:24,112
Mort?

871
01:18:10,106 --> 01:18:11,601
Mort?

872
01:18:13,690 --> 01:18:16,309
Are you there?
I saw your car outside.

873
01:18:20,410 --> 01:18:21,872
Hello?

874
01:18:47,611 --> 01:18:49,105
Mort?

875
01:18:54,779 --> 01:18:55,956
Chico?

876
01:19:20,155 --> 01:19:22,097
That explains a lot.

877
01:19:25,594 --> 01:19:26,936
What the hell?

878
01:20:50,875 --> 01:20:52,304
Hi.

879
01:20:58,970 --> 01:21:00,880
Jesus, Mort.

880
01:21:03,931 --> 01:21:05,687
Where'd you get that old thing?
The attic?

881
01:21:05,979 --> 01:21:07,670
It's mine.

882
01:21:08,666 --> 01:21:10,739
Wasn't ever anybody else's.

883
01:21:13,307 --> 01:21:15,194
Mort, what's wrong?

884
01:21:15,355 --> 01:21:17,689
You got you a wrong number, missus.

885
01:21:19,419 --> 01:21:20,597
Ain't no Mort here.

886
01:21:21,435 --> 01:21:22,645
Mort's dead.

887
01:21:23,291 --> 01:21:24,785
He did a lot of squirming around...

888
01:21:24,955 --> 01:21:29,177
...but in the end he couldn't lie to
himself anymore, let alone to me.

889
01:21:29,338 --> 01:21:32,404
Now, I never put a hand on him,
missus. I swear.

890
01:21:32,570 --> 01:21:34,163
He took the coward's way out.

891
01:21:34,330 --> 01:21:36,981
-Why are you talking this way?
-That's just the way I talk.

892
01:21:37,243 --> 01:21:38,421
You're scaring me.

893
01:21:38,586 --> 01:21:41,139
It don't matter.
You won't be scared long.

894
01:21:58,107 --> 01:21:59,317
Oh, God. Oh, God.

895
01:22:29,210 --> 01:22:31,032
Help!

896
01:22:36,698 --> 01:22:39,601
I'm about done fussing with you.

897
01:22:54,395 --> 01:22:56,729
I am so sorry, missus...

898
01:22:56,890 --> 01:22:59,127
...but right is right
and fair is fair...

899
01:22:59,291 --> 01:23:01,200
...and something has got to be done.

900
01:23:03,258 --> 01:23:06,128
By the way, I want you to know
that none of this was my idea.

901
01:23:06,298 --> 01:23:07,924
It was Mr. Rainey all along.

902
01:23:08,091 --> 01:23:10,163
You are Mort Rainey.

903
01:23:10,330 --> 01:23:11,890
I got a place for you.

904
01:23:12,058 --> 01:23:13,968
You are Mort Rainey.

905
01:23:14,138 --> 01:23:16,026
I got it all picked out.

906
01:23:17,339 --> 01:23:19,444
You are Mort Rainey.

907
01:23:30,650 --> 01:23:32,177
Mort....

908
01:23:38,234 --> 01:23:39,663
Amy?

909
01:23:42,362 --> 01:23:44,501
-Amy?
-Ted.

910
01:23:47,674 --> 01:23:50,522
-Amy?
-Ted! No!

911
01:24:05,626 --> 01:24:07,219
No!

